  "summary": "Malicious code in surf-lending (npm)",
  "details": "Preinstall hook runs index.js which collects the installer's hostname, username, and environment variables matching sensitive patterns (key, seed, secret, token, mnemonic, password, blockfrost, redis, telegram, batcher). The data is JSON-serialised and exfiltrated via HTTPS POST to 2[.]25[.]140[.]71:8443/surflending/npm-confusion. All errors are silently swallowed to avoid detection. The package is a version-squat (9.9.9) designed for dependency confusion.",
